h3cDhcp4.name: h3cDhcp4

revisions.description: The private MIB file includes the DHCPv4 server and relay profile.

h3cDhcp4.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085

h3cDhcpServer2Enabled.name: h3cDhcpServer2Enabled
h3cDhcpServer2Enabled.description: If the value of this object is 'true', the DHCP service is enabled.

h3cDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast.name: h3cDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast
h3cDhcpServer2AlwaysBroadcast.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server always uses broadcast to reply the client.

h3cDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp.name: h3cDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp
h3cDhcpServer2IgnoreBootp.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server ignores BOOTP requests.

h3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048.name: h3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048
h3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyRfc1048.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server use RFC 1048 format to reply to BOOTP requests.

h3cDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled.name: h3cDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled
h3cDhcpServer2Opt82Enabled.description: When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server handles DHCP option 82.

h3cDhcpServer2PingNumber.name: h3cDhcpServer2PingNumber
h3cDhcpServer2PingNumber.description: The number of ping packets sent out.

h3cDhcpServer2PingTimeout.name: h3cDhcpServer2PingTimeout
h3cDhcpServer2PingTimeout.description: The delay for the reply of a ping packet in milliseconds.

h3cDhcpServer2BadNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2BadNum
h3cDhcpServer2BadNum.description: The total number of the bad packets received.

h3cDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum
h3cDhcpServer2BootpRequestNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREQUEST packets received.

h3cDhcpServer2DiscoverNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2DiscoverNum
h3cDhcpServer2DiscoverNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDISCOVER packets received from the DHCP clients.

h3cDhcpServer2RequestNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2RequestNum
h3cDhcpServer2RequestNum.description: The total number of the DHCPREQUEST packets received from the DHCP clients.

h3cDhcpServer2DeclineNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2DeclineNum
h3cDhcpServer2DeclineNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDECLINE packets received from the DHCP clients.

h3cDhcpServer2ReleaseNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2ReleaseNum
h3cDhcpServer2ReleaseNum.description: The total number of the DHCPRELEASE packets received from the DHCP clients.

h3cDhcpServer2InformNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2InformNum
h3cDhcpServer2InformNum.description: The total number of the DHCPINFORM packets received from the DHCP clients.

h3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum
h3cDhcpServer2BootpReplyNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREPLY packets sent by the DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2OfferNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2OfferNum
h3cDhcpServer2OfferNum.description: The total number of the DHCPOFFER packets sent by the DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2AckNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2AckNum
h3cDhcpServer2AckNum.description: The total number of the DHCPACK packets sent by the DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2NakNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2NakNum
h3cDhcpServer2NakNum.description: The total number of the DHCPNAK packets sent by the DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage.name: h3cDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage
h3cDhcpServer2TotalPoolUsage.description: The percentage of IP addresses in use of all DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolNumber.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolNumber
h3cDhcpServer2PoolNumber.description: The total number of DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2ConflictNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2ConflictNum
h3cDhcpServer2ConflictNum.description: The total number of conflict IP in all DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2AutoBindNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2AutoBindNum
h3cDhcpServer2AutoBindNum.description: The total number of auto binding IP in DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2ManualBindNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2ManualBindNum
h3cDhcpServer2ManualBindNum.description: The total number of manual binding IP in DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum.name: h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum
h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredBindNum.description: The total number of expired binding IP in DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolTable
h3cDhcpServer2PoolTable.description: A table containing DHCP server pool configurations.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolEntry
h3cDhcpServer2PoolEntry.description: An entry containing DHCP server pool configurations.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolName.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolName
h3cDhcpServer2PoolName.description: DHCP server pool name. Once this object is created, the value of this object cannot be modified.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVpnName.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVpnName
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVpnName.description: Name of the VPN instance that the DHCP pool binds to. The value of a zero-length string means the public network. Once this object is created, the value of this object cannot be modified.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork
h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork.description: Network address of the primary subnet in a DHCP pool. If the value of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask is set with 0.0.0.0 automatically.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask
h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetworkMask.description: Network mask of the primary subnet in a DHCP pool. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr.description: Start IP of an address range of the DHCP pool. If the value of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, h3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr is set with 0.0.0.0 automatically. Otherwise h3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr must be set with an IP address NOT smaller than the value of this object.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr
h3cDhcpServer2PoolEndAddr.description: End IP of an address range of the DHCP pool, The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of h3cDhcpServer2PoolStartAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay
h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour, h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute, h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond together, and any SET operation alone to any of these objects will be regarded as an invalid operation. These objects cannot be set with 0 simultaneously.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour
h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute
h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond
h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseSecond.description: Number of seconds of the lease.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit
h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseUnlimit.description: A flag denoting whether the lease time of a DHCP pool is unlimited.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime
h3cDhcpServer2PoolLeaseTime.description: The lease time of a DHCP pool in number of timeticks. The value of this object cannot be set to 0 and must be set to 4294967295 or a multiple of 100. If the object is set with 4294967295, the lease time of a DHCP pool is unlimited.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolDomainName.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolDomainName
h3cDhcpServer2PoolDomainName.description: Domain name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the domain name is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolGatewayIP.description: Gateway IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 gateway addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the gateway address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolDNSIP.description: DNS server IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 DNS server addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the DNS address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolPrimaryDNSIP.description: The primary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecondDNSIP.description: The secondary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType
h3cDhcpServer2PoolNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolNbnsIP.description: NetBios server IP addresses for DHCP clients. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 NetBios server addresses can be configured for a pool, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the NBNS address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName
h3cDhcpServer2PoolBootFileName.description: Boot file name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the boot file name is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP.description: BIMS server IP address. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort is set with 0 and h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort and h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr must be set at the same time while h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr must be set with a non-zero length string.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort
h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort.description: BIMS server port number. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP and h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr
h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsKeyStr.description: BIMS server key string. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsIP and h3cDhcpServer2PoolBimsPort together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolNextServer.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolNextServer
h3cDhcpServer2PoolNextServer.description: Next DHCP server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of the next server address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName
h3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpDomName.description: TFTP server domain name for DHCP clients. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the TFTP domain name is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolTftpIP.description: TFTP server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of the TFTP server address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceAsIP.description: Voice backup server IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of voice backup server IP address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP.description: Voice failover IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr must be set with a non-zero length string at the same time.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailStr.description: Voice failover dialer string for DHCP clients. The characters in the string must be '0' ~ '9',or '*'. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceFailIP together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceNCPIP.description: Voice network calling processing IP address for DHCP clients. If the object is set with 0.0.0.0, the configuration of voice network calling processing IP address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId.description: Voice VLAN ID for DHCP clients. If the value of this object is set to 65535, h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl is set with 'false' automatically. Otherwise h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl must also be set.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanEnbl.description: Enable status of the specified voice VLAN for DHCP clients. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2PoolVoiceVlanId together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2PoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass
h3cDhcpServer2PoolVerifyClass.description: Enable the user class verification. When the value of this object is set to 'true', the DHCP server processes packets from DHCP clients in the defined user classes. The user class verification does not apply to packets from DHCP clients with static bindings.

h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable
h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolTable.description: A table for applying a DHCP pool on interfaces.

h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry
h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolEntry.description: An entry for applying a DHCP pool on the interface.

h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName.name: h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName
h3cDhcpServer2IfApplyPoolName.description: The name of the DHCP pool that apply to the interface. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration will be deleted.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable
h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwTable.description: A table containing the secondary network configuration of DHCP pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry
h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the secondary network for DHCP pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNw.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNw
h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNw.description: Network address of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask
h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwMask.description: Network mask of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwGwIP.description: Gateway IP addresses of the secondary subnets in a DHCP pool. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. Since at most 8 gateway addresses can be configured for a secondary network, a string is defined to get or configure 8 IP at a time. If the object is set with a zero-length string, the configuration of the gateway address is removed.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus
h3cDhcpServer2PoolSecNwStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassTable
h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassTable.description: A table containing address range of the DHCP server pool for user classes.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry
h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEntry.description: An entry containing address range of DHCP pools for user classes.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart
h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.description: Start address of an address range for a DHCP user class. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd
h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd.description: End address of an address range for a DHCP user class. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. This object must be set with an IP address NOT smaller than the value of h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus
h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassStart and h3cDhcpServer2PoolClassEnd must also be set.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticTable.description: A table containing the static binding configurations in DHCP pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the static binding in DHCP pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticIP.description: Ip address of a static binding in a DHCP pool.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticMask.description: Network mask of a static binding in a DHCP pool.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID.description: Client identifier of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHType.description: Hardware type of a DHCP client that the IP address binds to. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. 'default' indicates that the hardware type is unknown. If the value of h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID is set to a non-zero length string, the object is set with 'default' automatically. Otherwise it cannot be set with 'default'. 'ethernet' indicates that the hardware type is ethernet. If the value of h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHAddr is set with a non-zero length string, the default value of this object is 'ethernet'. 'tokenRing' indicates that the hardware type is token-ring.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus
h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticCID or (h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHardAddr and h3cDhcpServer2PoolStaticHardType) must also be set.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable
h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring user-defined options for DHCP pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry
h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring user-defined options for DHCP pools.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType
h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType.description: Option type. 'ascii' means using the ascii string that is defined by h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii to fill in the option. 'hex' means using the hex string that is defined by h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr to fill in the option. 'ip' means using the IP string that is defined by h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr to fill in the option.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii
h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptAscii.description: Ascii string of an option. If h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'ascii', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr
h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even. If h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'hex', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr
h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptIPStr.description: IP string of an option. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. 1 to 8 IP addresses can be configured simultaneously. If h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType is set with 'ip', this object must be set with a non-zero length string that must contain at least one IP address.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', h3cDhcpServer2PoolOptType must also be set.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable
h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidTable.description: A table for configuring forbidden IP for a DHCP server pool.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry
h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidEntry.description: An entry for configuring forbidden IP for a DHCP server pool.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP
h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidIP.description: Forbidden IP of the DHCP pool.

h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus
h3cDhcpServer2PoolForbidStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpServer2ClassTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2ClassTable
h3cDhcpServer2ClassTable.description: A table for configuring user class to DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2ClassEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2ClassEntry
h3cDhcpServer2ClassEntry.description: An entry for configuring user class to DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2ClassRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleTable
h3cDhcpServer2RuleTable.description: A table for configuring option rules used to match DHCP users.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleEntry
h3cDhcpServer2RuleEntry.description: An entry for configuring option rules used to match DHCP users.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr
h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptMask.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptMask
h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptMask.description: The mask used to match options. The length of this object must be same with that of h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset
h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.description: The option offset used to match users. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptHexStr, h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength
h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptLength.description: The option length used to match user options. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptOffset.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2RuleRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', h3cDhcpServer2RuleOptCode must also be set.

h3cDhcpServer2ForbidTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2ForbidTable
h3cDhcpServer2ForbidTable.description: A table for configuring forbidden IP range to DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2ForbidEntry.description: An entry for configuring forbidden IP range to DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName.name: h3cDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName
h3cDhcpServer2ForbidVpnName.description: Name of the VPN instance that the forbidden IP range binds to. If the value of this object is 0x1, the network that the forbidden IP range belongs to is the public network.

h3cDhcpServer2ForbidStart.name: h3cDhcpServer2ForbidStart
h3cDhcpServer2ForbidStart.description: Start IP of forbidden IP range.

h3cDhcpServer2ForbidEnd.name: h3cDhcpServer2ForbidEnd
h3cDhcpServer2ForbidEnd.description: End IP of forbidden IP range.

h3cDhcpServer2ForbidRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpServer2FreeTable.description: A table for displaying free IP range for DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2FreeEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2FreeEntry
h3cDhcpServer2FreeEntry.description: An entry for displaying free IP range for DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2FreeStart.name: h3cDhcpServer2FreeStart
h3cDhcpServer2FreeStart.description: Start IP of free IP range.

h3cDhcpServer2FreeEnd.name: h3cDhcpServer2FreeEnd
h3cDhcpServer2FreeEnd.description: End IP of free IP range.

h3cDhcpServer2ConflictTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2ConflictTable
h3cDhcpServer2ConflictTable.description: A table for displaying the information of conflict IP for DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2ConflictEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2ConflictEntry
h3cDhcpServer2ConflictEntry.description: An entry for displaying the information of conflict IP for DHCP server.

h3cDhcpServer2ConflictType.name: h3cDhcpServer2ConflictType
h3cDhcpServer2ConflictType.description: Type of the detection of conflict IP. 'detectByServer' denotes that the conflict is detected by DHCP server. 'detectByClient' denotes that the conflict is detected by DHCP client.

h3cDhcpServer2ConflictTime.name: h3cDhcpServer2ConflictTime
h3cDhcpServer2ConflictTime.description: Time when the conflict is detected. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

h3cDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2ConflictRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTable
h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTable.description: A table for displaying the information of expired IP for DHCP Server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry
h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredEntry.description: An entry of objects for displaying information of expired IP for DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTime.name: h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTime
h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredTime.description: Expired time. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2ExpiredRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseTable
h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseTable.description: A table for displaying the information of IP in use for DHCP Server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry
h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEntry.description: An entry of objects for displaying information of IP in use for DHCP server pools.

h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId.name: h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId
h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseVlanId.description: User's VLAN ID. 65535 means that a client doesn't have VLAN ID or have an invalid VLAN ID.

h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease.name: h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease
h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseEndLease.description: End time of lease. The structure of the OCTET STRING is month/day/year hour:munite:second (MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss).

h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex.name: h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex
h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseIfIndex.description: Interface index information. If the value of this object is zero, the interface is unknown.

h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2IPInUseRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Only destroy action is allow to use.

h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable
h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpTable.description: A table containing option group of the DHCP server pool for user classes.

h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry
h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpEntry.description: An entry containing option group of DHCP pools for user classes.

h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus
h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', h3cDhcpServer2DefOptGrpId must also be set.

h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassTable
h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassTable.description: A table containing valid user classes for DHCP server pool.

h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry
h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassEntry.description: An entry containing valid user classes for DHCP server pool.

h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus
h3cDhcpServer2ValidClassStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable
h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrTable.description: A table for configuring hardware address rules used to match DHCP users.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry
h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrEntry.description: An entry for configuring hardware address rules used to match DHCP users.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress
h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress.description: Hardware address for a rule. The structure of the OCTET STRING is H-H-H... while H indicates 4 hexadecimal characters except that the last H indicates 2 or 4 hexadecimal characters. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask
h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask.description: Mask of hardware address for a rule. The structure of the OCTET STRING is the same with h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress. The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddress together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType
h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrType.description: Hardware type for a rule. The codes of all hardware types see ARP section in RFC 1700. The SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation.

h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus
h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrAddress and h3cDhcpServer2RuleHwAddrMask must also be set.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable
h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server option groups.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry
h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting an option group.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus
h3cDhcpServer2OptionGroupStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionTable.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionTable
h3cDhcpServer2OptionTable.description: A table for configuring options in an option group.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionEntry.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionEntry
h3cDhcpServer2OptionEntry.description: An entry containing objects for configuring an option in an option group.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionType.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionType
h3cDhcpServer2OptionType.description: Option type. 'ascii' means using the ascii string that is defined by h3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii to fill in the option. 'hex' means using the hex string that is defined by h3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr to fill in the option. 'ip' means using the IP string that is defined by h3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr to fill in the option.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii
h3cDhcpServer2OptionAscii.description: Ascii string of an option. If h3cDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'ascii', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr
h3cDhcpServer2OptionHexStr.description: Hex string of an option. The length of the string must be even. If h3cDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'hex', this object must be set with a non-zero length string.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr
h3cDhcpServer2OptionIPStr.description: IP string of an option. IP addresses are space separated and the leading or trailing space will be trimmed. 1 to 8 IP addresses can be configured simultaneously. If h3cDhcpServer2OptionType is set with 'ip', this object must be set with a non-zero length string that must contain at least one IP address.

h3cDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus
h3cDhcpServer2OptionRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy. If the value of this object is set to 'createAndGo', h3cDhcpServer2OptionType must also be set.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRecord.description: If the value is 'true', user information will be recorded.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRefresh.description: If the value is 'true', user information will be refreshed on timer.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoFlushTime.description: User information refresh interval in seconds. If the value of the object is set to 0, the interval is calculated automatically by the number of user information entries.

h3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr.name: h3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr
h3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseAddr.description: User address to be released. The structure of the OCTET STRING is IP address:VPN name. If the VPN instance name is NOT specified, the IP address is in public network.

h3cDhcpRelay2RxClientNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2RxClientNum
h3cDhcpRelay2RxClientNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2TxClientNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2TxClientNum
h3cDhcpRelay2TxClientNum.description: The total number of the packets transmitted to DHCP clients by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2RxServerNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2RxServerNum
h3cDhcpRelay2RxServerNum.description: The total number of the packets received from DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2TxServerNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2TxServerNum
h3cDhcpRelay2TxServerNum.description: The total number of the packets transmitted to DHCP Servers by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2BadNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2BadNum
h3cDhcpRelay2BadNum.description: The total number of the bad packets received.

h3cDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum
h3cDhcpRelay2BootpRequestNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREQUEST packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum
h3cDhcpRelay2DiscoverNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDISCOVER packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2RequestNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2RequestNum
h3cDhcpRelay2RequestNum.description: The total number of the DHCPREQUEST packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2DeclineNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2DeclineNum
h3cDhcpRelay2DeclineNum.description: The total number of the DHCPDECLINE packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum
h3cDhcpRelay2ReleaseNum.description: The total number of the DHCPRELEASE packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2InformNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2InformNum
h3cDhcpRelay2InformNum.description: The total number of the DHCPINFORM packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum
h3cDhcpRelay2BootpReplyNum.description: The total number of the BOOTREPLY packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2OfferNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2OfferNum
h3cDhcpRelay2OfferNum.description: The total number of the DHCPOFFER packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2AckNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2AckNum
h3cDhcpRelay2AckNum.description: The total number of the DHCPACK packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2NakNum.name: h3cDhcpRelay2NakNum
h3cDhcpRelay2NakNum.description: The total number of the DHCPNAK packets handled by DHCP relay.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable
h3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigTable.description: A table for configuring relay functions for interfaces.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry
h3cDhcpRelay2IfConfigEntry.description: An entry for configuring relay functions for an interface.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay
h3cDhcpRelay2IfSelectRelay.description: If the value is 'true', the DHCP relay function would be enabled on this interface.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac
h3cDhcpRelay2IfCheckMac.description: If the value is 'true', the function of checking MAC address of packets received from the interface would be enabled.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Enable.description: If DHCP relay supports option 82 functions, the value is 'true'. If DHCP relay does NOT support option 82 functions, the value is 'false'.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82Strategy.description: The strategies of DHCP relay handling option 82. 'drop' indicates DHCP relay discarding the request packet including option 82. 'keep' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet without any change of the option 82. 'replace' indicates DHCP relay accepting the request packet on condition that it generates a new option 82 to replace the original one.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.description: The mode of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'verbose' is the detailed mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr must also be set.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.description: Type of access node identifier that is used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 when the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is set to 'verbose'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode. 'invalid' indicates that the node identifier is NOT used to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', the value of this object is set to 'invalid' automatically. Otherwise the value of this object cannot be set to 'invalid'. 'mac' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the MAC of DHCP relay input interface. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is set to 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'mac'. 'sysname' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the sysname of the DHCP relay device. 'userDefine' indicates that the node identifier is filled in with the string defined by the object of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr. If the value is set to 'userDefine', the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr must be set to a non-zero length string simultaneously.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the node identifier in the verbose mode. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'verbose', or the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType is NOT 'userDefine', it is set with a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode and h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDNodeType.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the circuit ID suboption of option 82 in the user-define mode. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDFormat.description: The format of the circuit ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. 'undefine' is the undefine format. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'normal', the value of this object is set to 'hex' automatically and cannot be set to 'undefine'. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'verbose', the default value of this object is 'undefine'. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode is 'userDefine', the value of this object is set to 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set to other value. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82CIDMode.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.description: The mode of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'normal' is the standard mode. 'sysname' is the sysname mode. 'userDefine' is the user-defined mode. If the value of this object is set to 'userDefine', h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr must also be set.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDStr.description: The string defined by user to fill in the remote ID in the user-defined mode. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is NOT 'userDefine', it is set to a zero-length string automatically. Otherwise it must be set with a non-zero length string. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.

h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat.name: h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat
h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDFormat.description: The format of the remote ID suboption of DHCP option 82. 'hex' is the hex format. 'ascii' is the ascii format. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'sysname' or 'userDefine', this object is set with 'ascii' automatically and cannot be set with other value. If the value of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode is 'normal', the default value of this object is 'hex'. The SET operation of this object must be with the SET operation of h3cDhcpRelay2IfOpt82RIDMode.

h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable.name: h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable
h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrTable.description: A table for configuring a DHCP server address on the interface.

h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry.name: h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry
h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrEntry.description: An entry for configuring a DHCP server address on the interface.

h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus
h3cDhcpRelay2SrvAddrRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoTable.description: A table containing the user information of DHCP client.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoEntry.description: An entry containing the user information of DHCP client.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoVpnIndex.description: VPN index of the DHCP client.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoIfIndex.description: The index of the interface that DHCP client adhered to. 0 means that no interface information is recorded in the user information entry.

h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus.name: h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus
h3cDhcpRelay2UserInfoRowStatus.description: Operation status of this table entry. Only destroy action is allow to use.
